section.section:
Except as provided in paragraph (2) of this subsection, the Commissioner shall assess each banking institution the sum of:
$8,000; plus
12 cents for each $1,000 of the assets of the institution over $50,000,000, but not more than $250,000,000;
10 cents for each $1,000 of assets over $250,000,000, but not more than $500,000,000;
9 cents for each $1,000 of assets over $500,000,000, but not more than $1,000,000,000;
8 cents for each $1,000 of assets over $1,000,000,000, but not more than $10,000,000,000; and
7 cents for each $1,000 of assets over $10,000,000,000.

If a banking institution is not in the business of accepting deposits or retaining funds in a deposit account as defined in § 5-509 of this title, the Commissioner shall assess the banking institution the sum of:
$5,000; plus
0.3 cents for each $1,000 of managed assets held in a fiduciary capacity up to $5,000,000,000;
0.2 cents for each $1,000 of managed assets held in a fiduciary capacity over $5,000,000,000, but not more than $20,000,000,000;
0.1 cent for each $1,000 of managed assets held in a fiduciary capacity over $20,000,000,000 up to $27,500,000,000;
0.2 cents for each $1,000 of nonmanaged and custodial assets held in a fiduciary capacity up to $5,000,000,000; and
0.1 cent for each $1,000 of nonmanaged and custodial assets held in a fiduciary capacity over $5,000,000,000 up to $20,000,000,000.
